name: Governor John Carney
tweet: In recognition of the passing of former State Senator Bob Venables and former State Senator and Representative Winnie Spence, I've ordered the Delaware flag to be flown at half-staff through Sunday, January 2.  https://t.co/VPrOsXiSsC

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: It’s important Delawareans do their part to slow the spread. Stay home if you’re sick. Wear your mask in public settings. Get your vaccine.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: The most important thing you can do to help slow the spread is get vaccinated and boosted. Vaccinations are proven to dramatically decrease the possibility of hospitalization and serious illness.

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: Hospitals are facing a very serious situation with the COVID surge this winter.  All DE hospitals have postponed elective surgeries, and you may face long delays in the event you need emergency care.  How can you help? ✔️Wear a mask in public ✔️Get vaccinated ✔️Get your booster  https://t.co/QsXnuXOGVm

name: Governor John Carney
tweet: 71% of COVID-19 hospitalizations from Dec. 6 to Dec. 12 were unvaccinated or partially vaccinated individuals.   The numbers are clear.   Get vaccinated and get your booster when you’re eligible.  https://t.co/EcBuQqSrNK  https://t.co/owm45FN1cy
